<li><a href="http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/9202/why-does-bitcoin-use-two-hash-functions-sha-256-and-ripemd-160-to-create-an-ad">Why does Bitcoin use two hash functions (SHA-256 and RIPEMD-160) to create an address?</a></li>
<li><a href="http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/3609/can-an-sha256-hash-be-used-as-an-ecdsa-private-key">Can a SHA256 hash be used as an ECDSA private key?</a></li>
